title: Neds Corner - Birds
description: Area incorporating (ie. birds seen from) the Neds Corner property (Trust for Nature) and the adjoining Murray River frontage.

items.title: Certhionyx variegatus
items.content_text: A small flock (<10) feeding over the revegetation area near the Sturt Highway.

items.title: Barnardius zonarius barnardi
items.content_text: Feeding under exotic trees near the homestead.

items.title: Acanthiza nana
items.content_text: Secretive and difficult to photograph on this occasion.

items.title: Pomatostomus ruficeps
items.content_text: Captured on motion-sensor camera at bird bath.

items.title: Hirundo neoxena
items.content_text: On the roof of the shearers' quarters at Neds Corner. Nesting also in the same building.

items.title: Cacatua galerita
items.content_text: Curiously, not commonly encountered at Neds Corner.

items.title: Hydroprogne caspia
items.content_text: Hunting along the Potterwalkagee Creek and Murray River.

items.title: Epthianura albifrons
items.content_text: Ordinary photo (very long distance away) but confirms the species.

items.title: Plectorhyncha lanceolata
items.content_text: Feeding on grubs hidden behind the seeds in the large pods of the Brachychiton tree in front of the Neds Corner homestead.

items.title: Ardea pacifica
items.content_text: Ordinary pic but useful as confirmation of the record, a new record for the Neds Corner birds collection. Far away and flew off before I could get close.

items.title: Egretta novaehollandiae
items.content_text: Ordinary pic but useful as confirmation of the record, a new record for the Neds Corner birds collection. Far away and flew off before I could get close.

items.title: Phalacrocorax carbo
items.content_text: Photographed from the Neds Corner homestead.
